begin_memory_text: We talked about where we were located.  We also talked about the use of masks  It was prompted by her being in Texas.  Shes a believer in masks
middle_memory_text: During the middle of the conversation, we talked about careers, Christie works as a business project manager in property and casualty while I work in healthcare IT.  She was disappointed by the reduction of business travel.
end_memory_text: WE were running out of things to say.  She is getting out there going to a painting class with a friend and will shortly be visiting her family.  Since she has a virtual job I said she can really work from anywhere so I suggested trying to travel.
rest_of_day_open: The weather here is quite rainy so I see a lot of time in from of the computer.  I will try to take my usual five-mile walk in the morning.  I hope to play golf on dry days.  Other than that I will do some remote work.  It will just be another week of trying to stay safe. My wife and I will try to have a dinner or two out as well.  The week will go as good as can be expected.
critical_positive: What worked the best about the conversation was getting to know what about Christie.  Where she lived and what she did.   Her current situation.  What also worked well was relating to the use of masks and how we felt about the pandemic in general.  We seemed to be on the same page on the current state of affairs.
critical_negative: I definitely felt I did too much talking and not enough listening. That is what happens when I'm in a situation where I feel I have to talk.  Sometimes I think about filling the time. I should have asked more questions about her or we should have agreed to take turns.  That would have been best.

begin_memory_text: We spoke about Canada as Perry is currently living in Vancouver and he has dual citizenship.  We also spoke about Covid-19.  I mentioned how I visited Victoria (Vancouver Island) and Vancouver, other parts of Canada
middle_memory_text: We spoke about traveling and how I am a Texan who is not anti-mask.  He made comments that suggested he thinks Texans are more anti-mask/anti-Vax.  Mhy memory is more fuzzy about the middle part.
end_memory_text: We asked each other for our names as we realized we had not earlier, and I asked him what their plans for the weekend was, thinking about how the weekend is starting.  I mentioned painting with a twist and he encouraged me to travel if I can since I can work from anywhere
rest_of_day_open: I think my week will go well.  I am glad that this conversation partner showed up because my last 2 did not show up and that was frustrating, even though it was out of my control.  I think this weekend will be relaxing and productive, and I want to workout and use a face mask to relax and pamper myself.
critical_positive: I think we both tried to find commonalities and talked about open-ended, broad topics such as travel and where we lived/traveled.  I think he is a decent guy and he seemed like a chatterbox who enjoys talking.  So it took the pressure off me a bit, and we were able to talk without silence breaks.
critical_negative: I think he is more liberal and he mentioned CNN, and I also felt like he talked too much, trying to overtake the conversation at times.  I do not think he has bad intentions but rather he is used to talking and I think he likes to hear his own voice.  I think he recognized at one point that he could pause and let me speak.
